<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,483,260,287]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Teuchophorus bipilosus</emphasis>
Becker, 1908
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="J.M.Aldrich" authorityYear="1905" box="[655,810,261,288]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Sympycninae">Sympycninae</taxonomicName>
)— 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[847,1036,261,287]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
new to 
<collectingCountry box="[932,1036,261,287]" name="Portugal" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Portugal</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,332,647]" box="[151,557,332,359]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,332,359]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,332,647]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,368,395]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Distribution.</emphasis>
Restricted to the southwestern corner of Europe, including northern Atlantic islands; also North Africa. 
<collectingCountry box="[237,336,405,431]" name="Portugal" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: one northern (Trás-os-Montes e Alto Douro) and one southern province (Algarve).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,332,647]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,441,467]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Ecology.</emphasis>
The only two Portuguese specimens were recorded from riparian corridors, one with; 
<emphasis box="[1314,1348,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">e.g</emphasis>
., 
<taxonomicName authority=", Salix" authorityName="Salix" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Alnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glutinosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Alnus glutinosa</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[270,326,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Salix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., 
<taxonomicName box="[379,487,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Typha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[379,447,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Typha</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[500,626,477,503]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Mentha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[500,586,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Mentha</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[638,749,477,503]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[638,708,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Rubus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[809,943,477,503]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Cyperaceae</taxonomicName>
, and one bordered by 
<taxonomicName box="[1190,1332,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Fraxinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1190,1291,478,503]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fraxinus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1344,1436,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Populus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linneo" authorityYear="1753" box="[198,390,513,539]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Nerium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oleander">
<emphasis box="[198,390,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Nerium oleander</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[446,542,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[446,502,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Salix</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
Both streams crossed sclerophyll Mediterranean bushland. The ecology of this species in the rest of Europe is unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,332,647]" box="[199,456,584,611]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,584,611]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
2.3 (rare).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,332,647]" box="[199,539,620,647]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,620,647]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Activity period.</emphasis>
July, August.
</paragraph>
